@tristaZero I think the idea of hiding distributed transaction from users means that in sharding database cases, for example a INSERT SQL could be rewritten to more acutal SQLs to exeucte on the different backend databases, and Shardingsphere will handle the different type of transaction (LOCAL, XA or BASE) to make sure the consistent of data which means INSERT THEM ALL OR NOTHING. Correct me if I misundertand the transaction model of shardingsphere. @terrymanu 

And in term of XA support, I think the user would like to coordinate the database operation and others by the external Transaction Manager. For example, insert into db and send a message to MQ

```
tx.begin();
// the shardingsphere will insert into two backend databse accroding to the user_id sharding rule
ds.executeSQL("INSERT INTO t_user VALUES ('1', 'user1'), ('2', 'user2')");
jms.send("insert users");

tx.commit(); // tx.rollback();
```

If the Shardingsphere does not support XA, when user decide to rollback the transaction, the message will not be sent to MQ but the data have been inserted into database that could break the bussiness logic.

